sg4DUDr4cOiUq6iameNa1tV26xaV9JYsge0_2GWRxHClHHhCvo=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating H2 dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens if tests run against a repackaged H2 jar without the data.zip file. That's a fallback issue, and I wonder if changing the dependencies is too broad. Since H2's functionality might rely on data.zip, could I use configurations as substitutes? No, that doesn't seem right. Maybe adding sourceSets to main wouldn't help either. I’m also pondering if the order of classpath in tests places `build/resources/test` first.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating performance issues**\\n\\nI’m considering that when the native datazip is absent, it might impact the execution of a specific line. This could potentially improve the remaining lines in an external run if I implement native instrumentation. However, I also need to keep in mind that there's a prior reference to `getResource(\\\"/org/h2/server/web/res/_text_en.prop\\\")`, particularly if the datazip is absent around line 397. It seems there's complexity here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method modifications**\\n\\nI'm realizing that Method.invoke is something I need to uncover, but to reach it, I first need to pass getMethod; it feels a bit tangled. What should my answer be here? I'm thinking about modifying my approach. Maybe creating a `UtilsScaleForAvailableMemoryTest` could be a good direction to take. It seems like that could simplify things or get me closer to the solution. Let’s keep exploring these ideas!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting project settings**\\n\\nI'm considering using a directory instead of a jar for the H2 build, as it might not pack the `data.zip` in the source context. I wonder if tests could depend on source context classes—though it seems that's a no-go. Maybe we could include an absent `data.zip` in the test implementation files before the jar, but I'm not sure. I'l