[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating JDK options**\n\nI'm considering using the JDK option -XX:MaxRAMPercentage, but I'm a bit unsure if setting it high would be beneficial. The maxMemory can't exceed Long.MAX due to that cap, so -Xmx may not be the right choice. I wonder if running under SubstrateVM native could return Long.MAX_VALUE for Runtime.maxMemory if there’s no max heap set. Testing under Native Image might cover line 692 at native runtime, but I’ve seen reports saying this line remains uncovered after attempts, which is puzzling.\n\n**Exploring API limitations**\n\nI'm considering the limitations of this non-public API and whether I need to stay focused. One possibility is invoking `Runtime.maxMemory()` through a helper that returns Long.MAX_VALUE, which would modify the active class behavior in an isolated duplicate. However, this seems to complicate things since it hits a specific call site. I could manually edit the class file bytecode, but that feels overwhelming. Inspecting the bytecode with `javap` might be a more manageable route.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_013a99f7a9f718620169f99f466e7881928a3a338d4c33458b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-Z9TfCnqzFzAU_gTFajPrcJxDKTlqmKUhOkyeCuky3NmI_aT8byT1GuUjsigx_sXpOjTSopOXMt_ExaNYgo8B6zh_meuGzEDesISN8Y2VXexQ3viTCJtI4ukgFR5eC67Hu3oNj5HoJCyVJDR9sZ7QCV26FtlYqdQ2ELy5GHdovBk8mK9xmupsSOcWH3a9ehYM4xnGQf1EYb_45vdjPNf1jhqW2S50dM68pDR2YK2CA3168XBa9koYBHpTuHyx_-8VJgu1O4ebKz0DrVJwAx_dlyzQok4G5-b7slcV6NN0lKXk6nZzZqEOeSs0_7xAXajT-brjrkliuVKRgYSRjmKGisRg_mKI7yAuV94z_fxVVzaRPZa-fGV0rOuQWG9GYs4gwJnbA0mxAFdFsSwaVVOdGRBnxyg9hqf3oH2Z0KArZSe_Zm6x6rOxTeSYZ3DGw7VDhpH0H-7hPeyJ8JRx4EtqYx9CX0SoMzbF3WMNnzgRcTg1rOCp8isgpuO0W7UFMu_tm-jwhLcCV1v7OR-5fDdUpSgLlkske2OeH1iVh0z_rYZZ16oZesVAJyOkdVHGsPhNFdQT_PA0C7D6f-iSAYxKiN8rqfKtI17qC8mj4wAfQuizHVkn4ifYRCtAPK2tUsgSyNDOz5X8bPF6anxRSsxq7m7wheCNCcEpqXPfu18VAe-qimgTmwllCsxo93XP-zZYZkG